# HerCare App Implementation Plan (Phase 8)

Phase 8 closes the biggest remaining gap in the Wellness flow by implementing a true **Sleep Logging experience**. The UI flow docs call out Sleep as the next build priority, so this phase turns the current static sleep card into a fully usable logged workflow.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Dedicated Sleep Log Screen (`SleepLog.tsx`)
- Create a dedicated screen accessible from the Wellness tab.
- Add the fields described in the UI flow: sleep start, sleep end, quality, and notes.
- Return the user to Wellness after saving, matching the rest of the app's editor flows.

### 2. Sleep Persistence + Goal Awareness
- Establish a `hercare_sleep_logs` array in local storage.
- Save each new sleep entry with duration metadata so we can render useful summaries.
- Read the persisted sleep goal so the app can compare a logged night against the user's target.
- Activate the existing onboarding goal counters so sleep and hydration goals are actually adjustable and persisted.

### 3. Dynamic Sleep Summaries (`Wellness.tsx` and `Home.tsx`)
- Replace the static sleep card content in Wellness with the newest saved sleep log.
- Surface saved sleep duration in the Home wellness snapshot.
- Expand the Smart Insight logic so short or poor sleep can influence the dashboard message.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This phase upgrades Sleep from decorative UI into a functional, persistent flow that supports the Wellness and Home dashboards.
>
> Approval has already been given in this thread, so this plan is being executed immediately.

## Verification Plan
1. Open Wellness, tap `Log Sleep`, save a sleep entry, and confirm the Wellness card updates.
2. Return to Home and verify the sleep snapshot and insight reflect the saved sleep data.
3. Refresh the app and confirm the newest sleep log and goal values persist.
